articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Three Palestinian students attending U.S. colleges were shot on Saturday night in Burlington, Vermont, and were being treated for injuries on Sunday, according to the students' former school in the West Bank.
articles.title: Three Palestinian students attending US colleges shot and injured in Vermont

articles.author: Alasdair Pal
articles.description: Australia's top civil servant in its interior ministry was sacked on Monday after an inquiry found he breached impartiality rules.
articles.title: Australia PM fires a top bureaucrat over influence probe

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Unidentified armed individuals were believed to have seized the oil tanker Central Park in the Gulf of Aden on Sunday, a U.S. defence official said.
articles.title: Armed individuals seize Israeli-managed oil tanker in Gulf of Aden -US official

articles.author: Saurabh Sharma
articles.description: Indian rescuers began drilling vertically on Sunday from the top of a mountain under which 41 workers became trapped two weeks ago while working on a highway tunnel in the Himalayas, government officials said.
articles.title: Indian rescuers, two weeks after tunnel collapse, try new tack to reach 41 workers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: One person has died and 12 people were missing on Sunday after a cargo ship carrying salt with 14 crew on board sank off the island of Lesbos, the Greek coast guard said.
articles.title: Cargo ship sinks off Greek island, one dead, 12 missing

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Pope Francis will recite his weekly Angelus prayer on Sunday from the chapel of his Vatican residence instead of the usual venue overlooking St. Peter's Square, the Vatican said in a statement.
articles.title: Ailing pope to recite Sunday prayer from residence, not St. Peter's square

articles.author: Toby Sterling
articles.description: Veteran Dutch anti-Islam politician Geert Wilders on Saturday vowed to be prime minister of the Netherlands eventually, following an election in which his party won the most seats.
articles.title: Dutch politician Wilders vows 'I will be prime minister' on X

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Thirteen Israeli and four Thai nationals released from Hamas captivity arrived in Israel on Sunday and were set to be reunited with their families as part of a crucial hostage deal, which briefly risked falling apart due to a dispute over aid supplies.
articles.title: Hamas releases Israeli, Thai hostages under temporary truce

articles.author: Umaru Fofana
articles.description: Sierra Leone has declared a nationwide curfew after unidentified gunmen attacked a military barracks and attempted to break into an armoury in the capital, Freetown, the government said on Sunday.
articles.title: Sierra Leone declares nationwide curfew after attack on barracks

articles.author: David Stanway, David Kirton
articles.description: At a gleaming new metro station on the edge of Shenzhen, the local government is promoting "carbon coins" to commuters to earn and trade for shopping vouchers and travel cards in a push to get households to join China's fight against climate change.
articles.title: China turns to households in fight to slash carbon emissions
